  "label::failed_transfer": "",
  "label::get_disposable_virtual_card": "",
  "label::get_physical_card": "Questions about obtaining, activating, or managing a physical debit or credit card belong here. In addition, requests for information about the card's physical details or associated PIN (such as \"Where is my PIN?\") should be assigned here. If the question is about retrieving or resetting a forgotten account password/passcode, use passcode_forgotten instead.",
  "label::passcode_forgotten": "Use this category only when the user has forgotten their app or account login password or passcode and wants help resetting or recovering access. If the user's question relates to their card PIN or accessing card functions, use get_physical_card instead.",
  "label::pending_top_up": "",
  "label::pending_transfer": "Questions or statements about a money transfer that has already been initiated but has not yet arrived, completed, or cleared should be assigned here—especially when the user mentions a pending or delayed transfer and asks about its status or when it will complete. Use pending_transfer (not transfer_timing) when the timing concern is connected to a specific in-progress transfer. If the inquiry is about transfers in general rather than a specific pending one, use transfer_timing.",
  "label::receiving_money": "Questions about getting funds from others (such as salaries, payments, or transfers) that do not involve topping up by card go here. Assign here for inquiries about receiving money via bank transfer or deposit. If the question is about topping up an account using a debit or credit card (regardless of who initiates it), use topping_up_by_card instead.",
  "label::reverted_card_payment?": "",
  "label::top_up_by_cash_or_cheque": "",
  "label::top_up_reverted": "",
  "label::topping_up_by_card": "Questions about adding money to an account using a debit or credit card, including when someone else tops up the user's account with their card, belong here. Assign here if the main action is putting funds into the account via card, regardless of who is doing it. If the question is about receiving income, salary, or bank transfers into one's account, use receiving_money instead.",
  "label::transfer_fee_charged": "",
  "label::transfer_into_account": "",
  "label::transfer_timing": "Use this for questions about how long transfers typically take, transfer speed in general, or the time required for a type of transfer—without reference to a specific pending or delayed transaction. If the user is asking about the status or completion time of a particular transfer they have already initiated, use pending_transfer instead.",
  "label::verify_my_identity": "",
  "label::verify_source_of_funds": "",
